{"article_id":"KOrDHtICmCjHS5Ww","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Figures go against Trump","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"talk","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"of restarting economy ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"as other countries tighten controls","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"US may become next centre of coronavirus pandemic ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"says WHO","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The US could become the new centre of the global coronavirus pandemic ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"according to the World Health Organization ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"which said","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"case numbers were rising quickly there","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"even asDonald Trump talked of reopening the country for business .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"\" We are now seeing a very large acceleration in cases in the US .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"So it does have that potential","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"[ to become the centre of the pandemic ] , \"","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"the WHO spokeswoman Margaret Harris said .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"So far , 46,450 people in the US have become infected with the virus","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and there have been 593 deaths ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"according to the latest data from Johns Hopkins University .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"In Spain , meanwhile , the numbers","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"infected and tested","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"rose from 33,089 to 39,673 on Tuesday ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"according to the health ministry ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"while the death toll rose from 2,182 to 2,696 .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Health workers accounted for nearly 14 % of Spain ' s total reported cases as of Tuesday , up from 12 % the previous day ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"according to data","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"presented by the health emergency chief , Fernando Simon .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Trump acknowledged","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"that crucial healthcare supplies","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"to protect frontline staff","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"treating sick patients","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"were becoming difficult to obtain .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"In an early morning tweet , he said :","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"\" The world market for face masks and ventilators is crazy .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"We are helping the states to get equipment ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"but it is not easy . \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"while more US governors were urging people to stay at home ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Trump appeared to play down the crisis on Monday night .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"The president said","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"he was considering ways","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"to restart the economy in the coming weeks","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and wanted to avoid the pandemic becoming \" a long-lasting financial problem \" .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"It would not last as long as three or four months ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"\" Our country was not built","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"to be shut down , \"","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Trump said .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"\" This is not a country","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that was built for this . \"","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Trump ' s senior advisers referred to current government restrictions as a \" 15-day challenge \"","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"and pledged to revisit in a week ' s time the need for sweeping measures","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"to prevent the spread of the virus .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"The top coronavirus response official in Italy , the country with the highest death toll , attributed two successive declines in the daily death rate to a national lockdown","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"that appeared to be finally bearing fruit .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"But Angelo Borrelli also noted","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that the real number of infections was probably 10 times higher than the official count .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"He also said","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"the nation of 60 million was on course to overtake China ' s total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in a week .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"\" The measures","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"we took two weeks ago","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"are starting to have an effect , \"","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Borrelli said in an interview with La Repubblica .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"more data over the next few days will help understand","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"\" if the growth curve is really flattening \" .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"An estimated 1.7 billion people around the world have been ordered to remain at home","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"as governments take extreme measures","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"to protect their populations .","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"Britain became the latest country","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"to enter lockdown ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"after bans on movement came into force at midnight on Monday .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"France entered a two-month \" state of health emergency \" on Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"that provides a legal framework for existing confinement and restrictive measures","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"and allows the government to order further restrictions ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"including controlling the price of certain products","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and requisitioning people and property for the \" war \" effort .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"In Germany , Angela Merkel ' s cabinet presented a support package","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"worth hundreds of billions of euros","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"to cushion the impact of the crisis ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"in a departure from the country ' s commitment","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"to balance budgets .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Under the rescue measures , about €50bn is to be earmarked for small businesses and self-employed workers ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"who are to receive direct grants of up to €15,000 over three months .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"The Dutch government strengthened its containment measures ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"banning all public gatherings","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"regardless of size","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"until 1 June","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"and empowering mayors to close beaches , parks , campsites and other public spaces","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"if people are not respecting physical distancing rules .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Play Video 2:10","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"How do I know","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"if I have coronavirus","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and what happens next ?","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"- video explainer","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"South Africa reported more than 150 new cases ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"taking its tally to 554 , the highest in Africa ,","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"a day after it ordered a three-week lockdown .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"Thailand ' s leader said","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"he would invoke sweeping emergency powers in the face of surging infections .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Egypt declared a curfew from 7pm to 6am for two weeks","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"starting on Wednesday .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"The Cameroonian Afro-jazz musician Manu Dibango died in Paris","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"after catching coronavirus .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Best known for his 1972 song Soul Makossa ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"the 86-year-old saxophonist is one of the first global stars","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"to succumb to the disease .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Pakistan suspended six civil servants","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"after they posed for a selfie with a coronavirus patient in a quarantine centre .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"The selfie","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"- widely shared on social media -","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"pictured a group of men around the apparent patient ,","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"several of them","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"smiling broadly","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"and none wearing face masks .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Meanwhile , tens of millions of people","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"living in Hubei province , the centre of China ' s outbreak ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"were told","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"they would be able to resume travel from midnight","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"( 1600 GMT ) ,","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"except in the city of Wuhan .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"China claims to have largely brought its outbreak under control ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"reporting only imported cases of the virus and few or no new domestic cases in recent days .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"However , the claims have been questioned by residents and analysts ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"who note","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"that some hospitals are reportedly refusing to test for the virus ,","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"and that there are allegations of manipulated numbers and rumours of unreported cases .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"Additional reporting by Kim Willsher in Paris , Jennifer Rankin in Brussels and Helen Davidson in Sydney","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":253,"left":130,"right":252,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":130,"left":0,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":190,"right":251,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":190,"left":151,"right":189,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":131,"right":150